CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 29, 1969, pg. 15, reads: "ADMIRING THE WORK of noted artist Palmer Hayden (shown with one of his paintings in 'Legend of John Henry' collection) are six members of the sponsoring organization. They are (from left) Mrs. Joanne Bates, Mrs. Barbara Hale, Mrs. E. Boggs, Mrs. Maxine Whedbee and Mrs. Jayne Shelton."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Jo Anne Bates, Barbara Hale, artist Palmer Hayden standing next to his painting from "Legend of John Henry" series, E. Boggs, Maxine Whedbee, and Jayne Shelton, at Palmer Hayden exhibition in University Art Gallery, Frick Fine Arts Building, University of Pittsburgh
